{"article_id":"r2KY1XsFGdz0nT83","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Bernie Sanders has the money and momentum","depth":6},{"id":1,"text":"to keep his campaign going all the way through to the Democratic convention .","depth":6},{"id":2,"text":"But","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"if he ' s going to do it as anything other than an also-ran to Hillary Clinton ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"the Vermont Senator needs wins in contests like the ones","depth":8},{"id":5,"text":"coming Saturday .","depth":8},{"id":6,"text":"Washington state , Alaska and Hawaii all hold Democratic nomination contests on Saturday ,","depth":7},{"id":7,"text":"and Sanders has a fighting chance for a sweep .","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"All three states are holding caucuses , an activist-heavy format","depth":9},{"id":9,"text":"that Sanders has thrived on .","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"Washington state and Alaska are also heavy on white Democrats , a core Sanders constituency ,","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"and have relatively few African Americans .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"Hawaii is a wild card ,","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"given a lack of polling and campaign attention ,","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"but Clinton surrogates are already working","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"to deflate expectations .","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"The opportunity comes packaged with peril , however .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"In a race to 2,383 delegates , Clinton leads Sanders 1,690 to 946 .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"( Even if Superdelegates are discounted ,","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"she ' s still ahead by 303 pledged delegates . )","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"And","depth":8},{"id":21,"text":"after getting clobbered in the Midwest","depth":10},{"id":22,"text":"and beaten in Arizona ,","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Sanders is in danger","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"of sliding back into irrelevance","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"if he can ' t score wins in the states","depth":8},{"id":26,"text":"that lean in his favor .","depth":8},{"id":27,"text":"Win or lose ,","depth":6},{"id":28,"text":"Clinton or Sanders will sit with Saturday ' s consequences for a while .","depth":6},{"id":29,"text":"Other than April 5 ' s tilt in Wisconsin , the race goes into semi-hibernation ,","depth":6},{"id":30,"text":"without a major contest coming before New York ' s 291-delegate scrap April 19 .","depth":6},{"id":31,"text":"Democrats in three states on Saturday dole out 142 delegates Saturday .","depth":4},{"id":32,"text":"Here ' s are the risks , rewards and likely outcomes in Washington , Alaska and Hawaii .","depth":4},{"id":33,"text":"Only four states are left on the Democratic primary calendar with more delegates at stake than Washington ,","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"but right now neither candidate can claim to be the favorite","depth":9},{"id":35,"text":"to grab them .","depth":9},{"id":36,"text":"`` We 're kind of in a sweet spot in the calendar .","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"I mean","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"after us New Jersey , New York , Pennsylvania and California are the four biggest , ''","depth":11},{"id":39,"text":"Washington state Democratic Party chairman Jaxon Ravens said .","depth":10},{"id":40,"text":"`` A couple weeks before us and a couple weeks after us there 's an empty space .","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"I think","depth":7},{"id":42,"text":"the way","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"the race has shaped up","depth":10},{"id":44,"text":"is that one thing","depth":11},{"id":45,"text":"to remember","depth":11},{"id":46,"text":"is we 're not a winner take all ,","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"it 's proportional .","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"Clinton has the support of top Democrats there like Gov . Jay Inslee and Sen. Maria Cantwell ,","depth":8},{"id":49,"text":"has campaigned in the state","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"and she , former President Bill Clinton and Chelsea Clinton have held fundraisers in the state .","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"But Sanders has been campaigning aggressively ,","depth":7},{"id":52,"text":"The Vermont senator 's presidential campaign held a rally in Seattle 's Safeco Field on Friday , capacity over 50,000 ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"and a day earlier did an event at the SunDome in the Yakima Nation 's treaty territory .","depth":9},{"id":54,"text":"The campaign estimated","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"that 7,000 people were in attendance .","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"He was also recently endorsed by The Seattle Times , the state ' s most prominent newspaper .","depth":9},{"id":57,"text":"And they don ' t call it the \" Left Coast \" for nothing :","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"Sanders ' hopes to make hay in deeply progressive Seattle and other liberal areas along the state ' s western edge .","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"`` If Senator Sanders is ever going to do well ,","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"I think","depth":11},{"id":61,"text":"it would be in Washington , ''","depth":11},{"id":62,"text":"Inslee told this week .","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Both candidates , however , have a safety net :","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"Delegates in Democratic caucuses and primaries are awarded proportionally .","depth":6},{"id":65,"text":"And in a race","depth":7},{"id":66,"text":"expected to be tight ,","depth":7},{"id":67,"text":"neither candidate is going home empty handed .","depth":6},{"id":68,"text":"State Democratic officials are expecting huge turnout ,","depth":5},{"id":69,"text":"but they have a system in place","depth":7},{"id":70,"text":"that","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"they ' re hoping","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"will avoid the type of ballot-access debacle","depth":9},{"id":73,"text":"that struck Arizona last week .","depth":9},{"id":74,"text":"Ravens pointed to a new pre-check system for Democratic caucus voters","depth":8},{"id":75,"text":"the state party is using this year for the first time .","depth":8},{"id":76,"text":"The system essentially allows voters to fill out all the necessary information","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"voters need ahead of time","depth":10},{"id":78,"text":"to vote in the caucuses -","depth":9},{"id":79,"text":"similar to pre-checking for an airline flight .","depth":8},{"id":80,"text":"Polling is non-existent in Hawaii ,","depth":3},{"id":81,"text":"but local Democrats","depth":6},{"id":82,"text":"-even ones","depth":7},{"id":83,"text":"supporting Clinton -","depth":7},{"id":84,"text":"have a straightforward read on Saturday :","depth":5},{"id":85,"text":"A Sanders win is expected ,","depth":6},{"id":86,"text":"a Clinton victory is a shocker .","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"\" I ' d be surprised","depth":8},{"id":88,"text":"if he doesn ' t do very well , \"","depth":8},{"id":89,"text":"said Hawaii County Democratic Committee chairman Phil Barnes .","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"A top Democratic aide to a Hawaii lawmaker","depth":9},{"id":91,"text":"supporting Clinton","depth":9},{"id":92,"text":"put it more directly :","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"\" He 's going to crush us .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"He should win this thing 2-to-1 at least , \"","depth":10},{"id":95,"text":"the aide said of Sanders prospects .","depth":10},{"id":96,"text":"\" If we keep this below 65-35","depth":10},{"id":97,"text":"I 'd be shocked . \"","depth":10},{"id":98,"text":"The Sanders campaign is spending big in search of a blowout .","depth":6},{"id":99,"text":"In the last month , the Sanders campaign spent $ 230,000 on state TV and radio ads","depth":7},{"id":100,"text":"while the Clinton campaign has spent just $ 40,000 .","depth":7},{"id":101,"text":"The Vermont senator ' s campaign has also aggressively deployed Rep. Tulsi Gabbard ,","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"who left her position as a Democratic National Committee vice chairman","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"to endorse Sanders .","depth":7},{"id":104,"text":"The campaign is looking to take advantage of her popularity there","depth":7},{"id":105,"text":"and on Friday released a new ad","depth":8},{"id":106,"text":"describing her decision","depth":10},{"id":107,"text":"to join the military","depth":10},{"id":108,"text":"and lapping praise on Sanders ' foreign policy positions .","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"Clinton , however , still has the support of most of Hawaii ' s Democratic establishment .","depth":5},{"id":110,"text":"Big name Democrats like Sens . Brian Schatz and Mazie Hirono , as well as Rep. Colleen Hanabusa , are all supporting her .","depth":5},{"id":111,"text":"Gov . David Ige , the state ' s new governor","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"who ousted former Gov . Neil Abercrombie in 2014 ,","depth":9},{"id":113,"text":"is staying neutral","depth":8},{"id":114,"text":"- at least publicly .","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"\" He ' ll vote for Hillary","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"and I think","depth":9},{"id":117,"text":"when he goes up to Philadelphia","depth":10},{"id":118,"text":"I would be shocked","depth":11},{"id":119,"text":"if he didn ' t cast his vote","depth":12},{"id":120,"text":"[ for her ] as a super delegate , \"","depth":12},{"id":121,"text":"a top Democrat","depth":10},{"id":122,"text":"involved with the Clinton campaign in the state","depth":10},{"id":123,"text":"said .","depth":9},{"id":124,"text":"Multiple Democratic aides said","depth":8},{"id":125,"text":"the governor has been on some of the campaign ' s strategy calls in the state","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"but hasn ' t been willing to openly endorse Clinton yet .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"Still , Clinton ' s campaign did as much","depth":11},{"id":128,"text":"as it could","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"in the state ,","depth":10},{"id":130,"text":"the Democratic aide said .","depth":9},{"id":131,"text":"\" They ' ve done a little bit of mail , a little bit of digital .","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"They didn ' t send us a surrogate","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"and I think","depth":12},{"id":134,"text":"with all of that there is a real problem with enthusiasm especially for Clinton","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"because there hasn ' t been anything","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"to gin it up , \"","depth":12},{"id":137,"text":"the aide said .","depth":9},{"id":138,"text":"Clinton hasn ' t spent much time or energy in Alaska ,","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"and the Sanders campaign is hoping to pounce on what the Democratic frontrunner left for the taking .","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"The state is fertile ground for a Sanders :","depth":10},{"id":141,"text":"it ' s a majority white caucus state with an anti-establishment flavor .","depth":11},{"id":142,"text":"The state also went for Obama over Clinton in 2008 ,","depth":12},{"id":143,"text":"and the Sanders campaign has spent $ 61,000 on TV and radio advertising in March","depth":13},{"id":144,"text":"while Clinton has not spent any money .","depth":13},{"id":145,"text":"The larger view among Democrats though is that","depth":11},{"id":146,"text":"while Clinton is popular","depth":12},{"id":147,"text":"there ' s more enthusiasm toward Sanders .","depth":12},{"id":148,"text":"\" Bernie Sanders has been doing a very good job with his ground game here , \"","depth":12},{"id":149,"text":"Alaska House Minority Leader Chris Tuck","depth":14},{"id":150,"text":"( D )","depth":14},{"id":151,"text":"said ,","depth":13},{"id":152,"text":"going on to say","depth":12},{"id":153,"text":"the state has an anti-establishment inclination","depth":13},{"id":154,"text":"and \" we also get upset with Wall Street and some of the banking bailouts","depth":15},{"id":155,"text":"so that plays a huge factor too .","depth":15},{"id":156,"text":"That plays into Sanders ' support . \"","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"Neither candidate has really campaigned there at all","depth":11},{"id":158,"text":"but Jane Sanders , the senator ' s wife , did a town hall over the weekend","depth":12},{"id":159,"text":"and that was a boost for Sanders , more so","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"than it would be in other states ,","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"said Jim Lottsfeldt , the former senior adviser to the pro-Mark Begich Put Alaska First PAC .","depth":10},{"id":162,"text":"\" We never , never get a taste of a candidate here , \"","depth":12},{"id":163,"text":"Lottsfeldt said .","depth":12},{"id":164,"text":"\" So actually having [ Sanders ' ] wife here this weekend is huge .","depth":11},{"id":165,"text":"I suspect","depth":13},{"id":166,"text":"he 's going to do well","depth":13},{"id":167,"text":"but I know","depth":13},{"id":168,"text":"that the mainstream I-show-up-to-every-meeting Democrat seems to be for Hillary .","depth":13},{"id":169,"text":"So I could be wrong","depth":12},{"id":170,"text":"but it just feels like there 's more enthusiasm for Bernie Sanders . \"","depth":12},{"id":171,"text":"The Clinton campaign hasn ' t left the state totally off its radar though.","depth":5},{"id":172,"text":"On Friday the campaign released a robocall by former President Bill Clinton across the state","depth":6},{"id":173,"text":"encouraging Democrats to vote .","depth":6}],"relations":[{"parent":347,"left":253,"right":346,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":253,"left":205,"right":252,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":205,"left":200,"right":204,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":200,"left":179,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":179,"left":175,"right":178,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":175,"left":0,"right":1,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":178,"left":2,"right":177,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":177,"left":3,"right":176,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":176,"left":4,"right":5,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":199,"left":188,"right":198,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":188,"left":180,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":180,"left":6,"right":7,"relation":"context","nuclearit